==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pin-eyed
<hw>Pin"-eyed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the stigma visible at the throad of a gamopetalous corolla,
while the stamens are concealed in the tube; -- said of dimorphous
flowers. The opposite of <ant>thrum-eyed</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinfeather</ent>⟦br⟧
